
1. Go to locale and run install.sh

   cd locale
   ./install.sh

2. (Optional) Open /etc/locale.alias and make sure si and
   si_LK entries are in alphabetically correct place.

3. Install the font lklug.otf.  See fonts/README.fonts for
   step by step instructions.

4. Go to po/ directory and run si.sh

   cd po/
   ./si.sh

5. Recompile pango to your system using patches in
   rendering/pango.  Creating DEB and RPM packages are
   explained in doc/README.deb and doc/README.rpm.

6. Install gtk keyboard method in keyboard/gtk-im/.  Running
   autogen.sh (step 2) is not necessary if the `configure'
   script is already there.

   cd keyboard/gtk-im/
   ./autogen.sh
   ./configure
   make
   su -c make install
   make clean

